Body:
I want to create a combination between a standard telemetry graph and a graph with non-telemetric values spread over a time axis.

I have a number of examples of graphs for example: not telemetric data example

I thought to use either a bullet graph or in the x range. But I was able to use these in a way that is synchronized with the normal graph.

Ö¿I am happy to hear ideas for a similar solution

"

To combine, such types of the series, you have to at lest create separate x axes. You can also create separate charts or panes.

Highcharts.chart('container', {	  xAxis: [{	    type: 'datetime'	  }, {	    type: 'linear'	  }],	  series: [{	    type: 'xrange',	    xAxis: 0,	    data: [{	      x: Date.UTC(2014, 10, 21),	      x2: Date.UTC(2014, 11, 2),	      y: 1,	    }, {	      x: Date.UTC(2014, 11, 2),	      x2: Date.UTC(2014, 11, 5),	      y: 1	    }]	  }, {	    type: 'line',	    data: [2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2],	    xAxis: 1	  }]	});

Live demo: http://jsfiddle.net/BlackLabel/j57q0z9n/

"
